# Hermes Mobile — prevent recurrence (July 2026)

Full playbook: [hermes-mobile/docs/PREVENT-RECURRENCE-JULY-2026.md](../../hermes-mobile/docs/PREVENT-RECURRENCE-JULY-2026.md).

## Cursor single-pass (no duplicate subagents)

- Do **not** spawn subagents for the same file domain, PR merge, or research already done in the parent turn.
- Check `plan.md` §2 before `Task` — if `(in_progress)` by another agent, **STOP** or hand off via vault `Handoffs/`.
- One parent per lock domain; parallelize **disjoint** files only.

## Session gates (agent runs — never user homework)

1. Vault pull + newest `Handoffs/` before multi-file Hermes work.
2. `bash hermes-mobile/scripts/agent-adb-refresh.sh` before phone/pair claims.
3. `bash hermes-mobile/scripts/agent-pre-asc-edit.sh` before any ASC review notes edit.
4. Read `hermes-mobile/docs/proofs/continuous/latest.json` before "fixed" / "works on device".
5. `node tools/agent-session-start.js --full` before ship language.

## Hard bans

- ASC notes: no gateway URLs, tailnet hostnames, or API keys — `hermes://setup?demo=1` only.
- Multi-Mac: `node tools/hermes-mobile-pair.js --mini-tailscale` — never laptop `.env` key on mini URL.
- If `e2e=skipped` in `latest.json`, report it — do not claim device UX verified.
